Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.89,0:00:05.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte and Luise swapped places.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.86,0:00:08.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte had become Luise,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.44,0:00:11.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and is heading to Vienna to meet her father.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.07,0:00:14.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise had become Lotte
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.27,0:00:17.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and is rushing to Munich for a meeting with mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.23,0:00:22.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Two little twin sisters \Nembarked on a grand adventure.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.34,0:00:28.35,Sign,,0,0,105,,{\c&HEAFCF9&\bord0\blur0.8}Episode 5 \N {\fs35} Long Day for the Twins {ふたごの長い一日} \N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N {\fs23}\h      Translation: Perevodildo    |    Timings: Sub-RoRo \h
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.03,0:00:44.86,Default,,0,0,0,,"Dad's atelier is in a one-room apartment\Nalong Kärntner Ring."
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.86,0:00:47.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Kärntner Ring...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.13,0:00:50.64,Default,,0,0,0,,"Dad may be a huge egotist. {conceit; vanity; pride; self-importance; egotism}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.64,0:00:53.96,Default,,0,0,0,,When music he composed himself is playing, \Nhe gets completely absorbed." {listening abstractedly; absentmindedly; absorbedly; vacantly}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.87,0:00:59.80,Default,,0,0,0,,However, while in the composing daze, \Nhe is always grumpy and irritable.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.80,0:01:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And God save you, \Nif you try to talk to him at such a time.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.64,0:01:08.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Conversely, if the composing is going smoothly, he breaks into the room in the dead of night to pepper me with kisses. {/for a storm of kisses}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.20,0:01:11.09,Default,,0,0,0,,But then, he also reeks of alcohol a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.53,0:01:16.26,Default,,0,0,0,,That would be our dad, one word - an oddball!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.26,0:01:19.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Will I really be able to get along with dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.93,0:01:22.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Especially, if he reeks of alcohol?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.04,0:01:29.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Christine, you can't have this!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.68,0:01:32.53,Default,,0,0,0,,But come on! Even on the train, \Nyou only think of studying! {/while inside the train, you study it}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.53,0:01:34.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not being the usual Luise!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.25,0:01:35.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh? I'm not the usual Luise?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.96,0:01:37.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Mischievous and insubordinate tomboy! {unmanageable person (esp. a woman); shrew; stubborn tomboy}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.82,0:01:39.87,Default,,0,0,0,,The teachers' bane Luise Palfy. {annoyance (to); bane (of); constant worry (to)}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.52,0:01:42.86,Default,,0,0,0,,What's that talk? \NI'm the most usual myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.86,0:01:43.94,Default,,0,0,0,,See? See?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.44,0:01:48.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Ouch!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.31,0:01:49.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Even more strange!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.23,0:01:50.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe you need a break? {lit is "you look like you're overdoing it" but I think she means "you're tired"}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.05,0:01:52.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Monica, sorry, sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.20,0:01:58.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm so awkward in this role! {/no confidence after all}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.09,0:02:00.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone finding out is a question of time! {/I can't trick everyone well}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.34,0:02:02.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Probably, with dad in the vanguard! {/will definitely find otu}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.00,0:02:05.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I've had enough already. \NI want to run away!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.94,0:02:08.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise, how have you been doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.64,0:02:12.55,Sign,,0,0,0,,Munich Central Station
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.17,0:02:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's what Munich is like!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.00,0:02:30.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm finally here!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.54,0:02:35.10,Default,,0,0,0,,When mom shows up, before saying anything, \NI'll kiss her hard! Definitely!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.10,0:02:37.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder how it feels \Nto be kissing your mother?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.74,0:02:48.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise, you'll know it's mom \Nby her totally irresistible smell.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.89,0:02:50.76,Default,,0,0,0,,But first, you'll notice her yellow dress.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.76,0:02:52.16,Default,,0,0,0,,That'll be a surefire feature.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.16,0:02:55.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see. Yellow, yellow...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.44,0:03:05.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Mother!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.37,0:03:06.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Nina!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.73,0:03:08.30,Default,,0,0,0,,My, you look so fresh!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.30,0:03:09.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you like it in the summer camp?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.98,0:03:10.93,Default,,0,0,0,,You bet!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.33,0:03:13.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, it's just Nina's mom? She's pretty.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.79,0:03:17.31,Default,,0,0,0,,But it goes without saying, \Nmy own mom would be times as pretty!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.79,0:03:23.16,Sign,,0,0,0,,Vienna Western Station
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.97,0:03:31.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes! We're here! Vienna!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.58,0:03:32.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Been a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.54,0:03:41.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Look, Luise! \NYour dad is already here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.02,0:03:42.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Right there!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.94,0:03:46.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Handsome whenever I get to see him, \NLuise's dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.21,0:03:48.08,Default,,0,0,0,,No less from a famous Viennese composer!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.08,0:03:51.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You're lucky. Wish I had a dad like that, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.09,0:03:53.29,Default,,0,0,0,,This is him... my dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.82,0:03:57.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The gentleman down the platform, \NI think, is Herr Ludwig Palfy himself!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.26,0:04:00.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Indeed! Ladies, shall we go pay our respects?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.35,0:04:04.13,Default,,0,0,0,,My! If it isn't Herr Palfy.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.85,0:04:07.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I am infinitely honored to meet you! {it's a honor to be recognized (esp. by someone of higher status); to be visible; to be seen; to be noticed​}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.59,0:04:07.29,Default,,0,0,0,,No need...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.07,0:04:09.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I have listened to your every opera!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.30,0:04:11.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Master, your genius is unquestionable!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.77,0:04:11.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... Yeah. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.04,0:04:12.77,Default,,0,0,0,,But I'm meeting my daughter from this train.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.77,0:04:14.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! Luise, this way!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.51,0:04:19.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Just as I thought. \NHe is not some scary bogeyman.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.09,0:04:31.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me, could you? \NI need to get to him, please...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.03,0:04:41.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me! Please let me through!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.77,0:04:51.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Please let me through!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.72,0:05:01.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Ladies! Silence, please!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.32,0:05:05.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Luise! Welcome back.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.69,0:05:10.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean... all that humbug at a place like this \Nmight deliver someone a nuisance.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.45,0:05:13.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I humbly ask you \Nto show some decency and etiquette. {/please mind your manners and etiquette}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.09,0:05:13.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.09,0:05:16.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Decency? Etiquette?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.23,0:05:20.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Did I hear that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.91,0:05:28.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm so sorry I'm late, my dear!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.75,0:05:29.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Mama!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.47,0:05:30.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You must be sick of waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.84,0:05:33.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, let's head home. \NDid you like it in the summer camp?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.68,0:05:35.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I loved every minute of it!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.18,0:05:36.69,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what I wanted to hear!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.93,0:05:44.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought, I'd be already \Nlavishing mom with kisses by now. { with all my might}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.86,0:05:48.07,Default,,0,0,0,,But mom still... {guess}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.34,0:06:00.54,Sign,,0,0,0,,Munich Graph Magazine
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.64,0:06:09.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, how many more times \Ndo I have to tell you, Editor Bernau?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.92,0:06:14.14,Default,,0,0,0,,This week's top article is the grand success \Nof a women rights activist! Nothing else is even close! {being very active; being very useful; playing a very active part; making a spectacular showing; great efforts; splendid work​ of woman lawyer, we don't have any more than this - unsure about last part}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.14,0:06:18.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I got it, got it. But for the top article, you should be choosing \Nsomething more eye-catching, Missis Körner.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.56,0:06:19.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Miss Körner!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.62,0:06:22.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the first time I'm meeting a woman \Nas headstrong as you!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.50,0:06:24.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Which one of us is headstrong here?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.29,0:06:27.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Women rights have been the talk of the town \Nin the recent years! {/from now on, woman should be more and more being very active; being very useful; playing a very active part; making a spectacular showing; great efforts; splendid work​ - it's that kind of time}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.66,0:06:30.34,Default,,0,0,0,,All I do is ensuring our magazine \Nkeeps up with the trend!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.34,0:06:33.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, but because of all this, \NI am now indecently late!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.54,0:06:36.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I was supposed to pick my daughter up \Nback from vacations.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.15,0:06:37.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, my poor Lotte.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.44,0:06:39.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait, the matter is not solved yet! {conclusion (of an argument, discussion, study, etc.)}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.02,0:06:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,No way I make her wait any more than that!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.00,0:06:43.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you running away \Nbecause you can't handle the job?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.31,0:06:45.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Running away? \NDon't say nonsense.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.06,0:06:46.99,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll settle it when I'm back in two hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.99,0:06:50.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Until then, don't you decide on it without me, {/let's continue this talk then} \NHerr Headstrong Editor-in-chief!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.49,0:06:52.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you kidding me?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.77,0:06:55.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Any other chief would have fired her long ago! {very unsure what he means: this way/with this, if I/you can't do the job, already would be fired - maybe he means I'm supposed to have fired her long ago}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.49,0:07:05.74,Default,,0,0,0,,This magnificent man... my dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.67,0:07:08.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to make a talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.47,0:07:10.17,Default,,0,0,0,,But what do I say?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.41,0:07:12.58,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it, Luise?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.92,0:07:14.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Something's off with my face today?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.45,0:07:17.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.25,0:07:22.37,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just that we've not seen each other in a while \Nso I've been missing my dear dad and his face.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.69,0:07:27.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Glad to know my daughter \Ndidn't grow to detest my face in that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.42,0:07:29.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Enough a reason for me to be a happy dad. {discovery; detection; finding}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.18,0:07:32.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And yet, it's as though something's off.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.29,0:07:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,This relatively short time has been enough \Nto cause a barely perceptible change in you. {unsure why he says "small time" and small change since that would make sense and wouldn't be notable/significant enough to make a statement}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.00,0:07:39.79,Default,,0,0,0,,But I haven't changed one bit! \NI'm the same as always.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.79,0:07:43.48,Default,,0,0,0,,No. For starters, you're been sitting tight \Nthroughout the whole drive. {/you're in your seat for the entire time in the car}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.48,0:07:46.25,Default,,0,0,0,,No hint of usual jumping around, \Nfrolicking, excitement. {(looking around) restlessly; (looking) all around; goggling​}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.75,0:07:49.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Must be that I'm just a little tired after the train.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.32,0:07:52.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Add to that what you said before, \Nabout decency and etiquette.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.77,0:07:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Before, hearing such a thing \Nwould have led me to think you're out of your mind. {/i'd say, hearing something like that until now would have given me goosebumps - really struggling with this one, in english goosebumps are mainly used for excitement, not for being alarmed}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.72,0:08:00.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I know! You're playing a good child now \Nto ask me for a big favor in the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.44,0:08:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Either that, or some other conspiracy... {/secret}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.96,0:08:05.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Why would I need to conspire against you? {/there shouldn't any ... of the kind}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.26,0:08:08.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Thing is, summer camp girls knew some manners, \Nso it rubbed off on me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.78,0:08:11.50,Default,,0,0,0,,At summer camp, sure... But... manners?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.89,0:08:41.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.94,0:08:44.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.10,0:08:45.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.18,0:08:56.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.06,0:08:57.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh... Ouch.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.58,0:08:58.54,Default,,0,0,0,,You okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.59,0:09:04.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, my Lotte! Sorry I made you wait. \NYou're finally back! {/I wanted to see you}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.20,0:09:10.24,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.24,0:09:13.50,Default,,0,0,0,,While on the way, \NI made up my mind to kiss you before you do!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.74,0:09:14.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.90,0:09:21.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.18,0:09:31.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Good perfume.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.65,0:09:37.22,Default,,0,0,0,,My, was just one month away really enough to make \Nmy resolute little housekeeper so suddenly sentimental? {lit: person of firm character; stable person; gutsy person, little housewife in just a month without seeing each other is a big spoiled child}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.36,0:09:43.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, shall we get something good to eat \Nbefore returning home?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.33,0:09:45.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Can I have an omelette?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.70,0:09:47.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Did you say omelette?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.26,0:09:51.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure, no problem. \NWe'll take what you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.50,0:09:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Great!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.68,0:09:56.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom, love you! {/you're the best}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.35,0:10:09.64,Sign,,0,0,0,,Imperial Hotel
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.24,0:10:24.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? What's the matter, Luise?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.17,0:10:26.83,Default,,0,0,0,,It's your very first omelette today, \Nbut you barely touched it! {first (in a series); initial}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.19,0:10:29.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because... You see...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.48,0:10:31.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Thing is...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.65,0:10:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Very odd! Even when bedridden \Nwith a fever of 39 degrees, {unasareru is to cry out in one's sleep (e.g. from having a nightmare); to moan (in anguish) in one's sleep}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.20,0:10:37.85,Default,,0,0,0,,even when weeping \Nover a boyfriend breaking up with you, {what boyfriend can she have an 10? fuck if I know, maybe he means like general/supposed/hypothetical situation and not something she's actually been through; other suggestion, he is just calling any male friend a boyfriend to tease her or for fun or because he doesn't know full situtaion, looking at it from a grown-up perspective}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.85,0:10:40.30,Default,,0,0,0,,you would invariably empty \Nat least five plates of omelette. {to eat up (completely)}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.30,0:10:43.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, my tastes may have shifted a bit \Nwhile in summer camp.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.59,0:10:46.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? Tastes shifted in summer camp?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.92,0:10:49.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! I can't stand omelette.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.70,0:10:52.25,Default,,0,0,0,,No way I would ever make a convincing Luise.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.25,0:10:54.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh my, Luise, back already?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.87,0:10:57.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you enjoy your summer vacation?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.81,0:10:59.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Who is this man?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.57,0:11:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, I bet you'll never choose it \Nover being with your dad in Vienna.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.28,0:11:06.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I know! Always talking with his hand on his beard. {/while touching}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.85,0:11:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Herr Strobl, isn't it? The doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.44,0:11:10.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Nice to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.42,0:11:12.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Nice to meet me?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.08,0:11:15.35,Default,,0,0,0,,But I was somehow sure \Nyou and me are ancient friends!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.75,0:11:18.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Right... But we've not seen each other in a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.62,0:11:20.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's as though we meet for the first time. {lit: I feel a great newness}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.53,0:11:24.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Sublime! Such a great change \Nin just little more than a month.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.33,0:11:26.67,Default,,0,0,0,,A girl is well-behaved, refined and tender!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.67,0:11:28.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Exactly! A different person!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.54,0:11:32.47,Default,,0,0,0,,This immature susceptibility, a plasticity of soul, \Nwith excitements of youth! {lit: children's sensitivity; susceptibility is so soft/tender, with fresh and youthful; lively; vibrant; vivacious; juicy (e.g. fruit)​}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.47,0:11:34.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, the emotion is strong! \NIt's overwhelming! {/this feeling}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.76,0:11:36.23,Default,,0,0,0,,He's at it again. {/he's always like that}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.23,0:11:37.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}At it... again?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.53,0:11:40.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Childish subtlety as opposed to maturity... {/without adults}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.37,0:11:47.96,Default,,0,0,0,,This is it! It's this melody! \NThe name would be "Vivacity of Childhood." {fresh and youthful; lively; vibrant; vivacious; juicy (e.g. fruit)​}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.96,0:11:49.86,Default,,0,0,0,,No! "The Fickleness of Children."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.86,0:11:52.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Right. Before I forget, \Ngotta write it down in a score.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.29,0:11:53.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! But your meal...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.63,0:11:56.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... Herr Strobl, look after Luise, will you?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.20,0:11:58.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure, you can leave this to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.93,0:12:01.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Boy, serve the girl a dessert.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.47,0:12:02.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.72,0:12:09.48,Default,,0,0,0,,My, my. You may have changed somewhat, \Nbut there's nothing that can affect your dad. {/your dad haven;t changed}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.49,0:12:26.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we've arrived, Luise.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.73,0:12:30.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It's here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.76,0:12:32.84,Default,,0,0,0,,This is our home at Rotenturmstraße!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.84,0:12:34.47,Default,,0,0,0,,My father's house!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.84,0:12:36.70,Default,,0,0,0,,You haven't been here for over a month.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.70,0:12:39.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Must have been missing it? \NNow, come on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.98,0:12:47.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Those comic books are quite amusing! {kono manga?}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.45,0:12:51.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Who could that be? \NMaster is not supposed to be coming home today.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.79,0:12:55.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Resi, it's us! \NFraulein Luise is back!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.09,0:12:59.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Right! It's the day when young Fraulein returns!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.90,0:13:04.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello. {/Im back}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.90,0:13:06.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome back.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.29,0:13:11.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Herr Strobl, come inside for some tea, too. Please.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.02,0:13:13.17,Default,,0,0,0,,No, no, you will now have to excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.64,0:13:15.25,Default,,0,0,0,,See you later, Luise.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.25,0:13:17.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Farewell, Herr Strobl.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.48,0:13:24.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, Peperl! I'm back! {from de}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.49,0:13:29.05,Default,,0,0,0,,My, usually, he'd be jubilant beyond belief by now. {high spirits; gleeful mood}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.05,0:13:33.02,Default,,0,0,0,,How could you forget your master completely \Nafter not seeing her for just a month, you dense dog? {thickheaded; insensitive; dull; thick-skinned}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.49,0:13:36.72,Default,,0,0,0,,No big deal. I'll make friends with him again in no time. {/can't be helped}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.04,0:13:39.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't mind what she said, Peperl. \NYou're the shrewd one here. {clever; intelligent; bright; smart; wise; sensible; shrewd}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.86,0:13:44.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Want me to serve a lunch soon?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.05,0:13:46.30,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I've had my lunch already. {to finish; to make an end of; to get through with; to let end}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.30,0:13:48.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd like to rest a bit for now. {at leisure; in a relaxed manner; in a carefree manner; quietly; peacefully}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.41,0:13:57.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And here it's the living room. Pretty!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.83,0:13:58.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.16,0:14:02.14,Default,,0,0,0,,My, how did this happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.14,0:14:06.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Just as I've finally finished cleaning up, \NPeperl decides to give me more work! {/is a bad dog; rabid dog again}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.10,0:14:11.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte, be wary of her.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.54,0:14:12.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Resi is a big fat liar.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.91,0:14:15.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Her words and her actions seldom meet.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.23,0:14:19.27,Default,,0,0,0,,But she also said, \NResi is not a completely disagreeable person. {hard to dislike; impossible to hate; likeable}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.27,0:14:21.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Either way, I should \Nkeep my ears to the ground with her. {need for caution; need for care; requiring special attention}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.61,0:14:36.44,Default,,0,0,0,,That was a good restaurant.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.44,0:14:38.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't expect my Lotte to order an omelette...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.66,0:14:41.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Moreover, you ate five of them! \NDidn't see that coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.21,0:15:00.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, Lotte is home, for the first time in a month. {unsure what she means: for lotte, first in the month our home}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.93,0:15:08.54,Default,,0,0,0,,This is it. \NThis is my and mom's home.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.54,0:15:11.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Why wouldn't it be, you quirky child?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.23,0:15:13.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Just saying I'm happy. \NIt's been a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.13,0:15:14.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, you mind if I recheck everything?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.76,0:15:17.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Wanna make sure all the rooms are \Nwhere they were before the vacations.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.70,0:15:20.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure, why would I mind. \NNeed a guide to show you the way?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.69,0:15:22.37,Default,,0,0,0,,If that wouldn't bother you too much.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.97,0:15:24.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I like those manners. {obedient; meek; docile; unaffected}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.54,0:15:31.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Right. Here, as you may remember, we have a kitchen.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.97,0:15:37.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Behind there - toilet and bathroom, \Nand the bath itself, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.11,0:15:42.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Towels are all stored here, \Nfeel free to help yourself to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.62,0:15:47.22,Default,,0,0,0,,This place we both use for recreation - \Na living room, if you will. {place for relaxation and refreshment}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.00,0:15:56.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And a messy one at that!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.74,0:15:58.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I may have neglected it a bit, because of work.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.50,0:16:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Finally, here is the room for Lotte and me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.77,0:16:06.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I left your half exactly the way it was \Nbefore {you left for }the summer camp.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.51,0:16:13.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I am in Lotte's room.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.18,0:16:17.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And also, when I start living here \Nwith mom, my room, too! { to pass (time); to spend}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.56,0:16:22.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, and this here is mom's side.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.06,0:16:24.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Not the biggest room around, \Nbut enough for two. {lit: although confined, a castle for two}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.26,0:16:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope you find it comfortable. {to like; to prefer; to be pleased by​}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.62,0:16:27.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I absolutely like it!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.96,0:16:28.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's pretty!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.40,0:16:34.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you. When Lotte is beaming like that, \NI myself can't help but to rejoice, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.32,0:16:40.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been away for so long, I nearly forgot it. \NIt's as though I've never been here before! {/I feel a great novelty}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.58,0:16:43.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I'm quite certain \Nyou're nothing like my usual Lotte.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.29,0:16:47.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Normally, I'd think you're an adult in a girl's body. {/i feel you are a small adult}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.25,0:16:49.63,Default,,0,0,0,,But today's Lotte is a normal lively child again! {in a lively way; vividly; freshly; animatedly; actively; energetically}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.63,0:16:51.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Was it {\i1}that{\i0} fun in the summer camp?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.38,0:16:55.06,Default,,0,0,0,,We did this, we did that...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.06,0:16:58.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I wasn't sure how you'd react \Nto being sent alone to the summer camp.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.34,0:16:59.91,Default,,0,0,0,,But now all my worries are behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.91,0:17:03.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, just being here with my mother \Nis even more fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.66,0:17:05.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the same for me, Lotte.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.28,0:17:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll make sure we never part again.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.36,0:17:09.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh no, I completely forgot!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.48,0:17:10.54,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.54,0:17:12.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I have to meet the Headstrong Editor!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.41,0:17:13.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Headstrong Editor?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.64,0:17:15.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Editor-in-Chief of Munich Graph.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.84,0:17:17.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I need to return to the office now.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.93,0:17:22.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm so sorry. \NI promise to return as soon as I can.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.29,0:17:24.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Later, this evening, we'll play cards. {/when I'm back, together}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.09,0:17:25.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Cards? You promise?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.75,0:17:26.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be waiting, awake!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.97,0:17:28.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, later then.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.85,0:17:35.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Hooray! Playing cards with mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.00,0:17:42.61,Default,,0,0,0,,How odd. It's past nine already.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.61,0:17:44.04,Default,,0,0,0,,But she hasn't returned still.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.04,0:17:47.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Apparently, not keeping their promises \Nis inherent to all the grown-ups, not just dad. {/I'm used to ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.75,0:17:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Could it be because that Headstrong Editor-in-Chief \Nis not letting mom go?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.31,0:17:57.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte said he is a hearty old chap.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.92,0:17:59.36,Default,,0,0,0,,But so far, he just sounds mean. {/bullying}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.76,0:18:07.47,Default,,0,0,0,,You could use some coffee.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.73,0:18:08.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah? Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.95,0:18:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Today, your sweet daughter \Nfinally made it home, didn't she?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.64,0:18:15.37,Default,,0,0,0,,From this point, \NI could finish the manuscript for you. {manuscript; copy; draft; notes; contribution}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.37,0:18:17.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you wanna get home sooner?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.01,0:18:18.21,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.21,0:18:23.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Not after going through all the trouble of persuading you \Nto make women rights activist's success our top article.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.95,0:18:26.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I must now bring it to the completion myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.22,0:18:28.75,Default,,0,0,0,,My, my. There's no helping your obstinacy.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.75,0:18:32.39,Default,,0,0,0,,But I'm quite certain, with this, \NI'm earning your daughter's animosity.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.39,0:18:33.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, do your best then.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.72,0:18:35.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I expect a fine article.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.33,0:18:36.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.65,0:18:46.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, Lotte.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.63,0:18:50.84,Default,,0,0,0,,But I've no time to slack off. Fight, fight!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.52,0:18:55.78,Default,,0,0,0,,At this rate, by the time mom's back, \NI'll fall asleep already.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.87,0:18:57.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it's fine, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.96,0:19:00.12,Default,,0,0,0,,We're yet to have plenty of evenings together.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.12,0:19:02.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I know! I'll use that time to write to Lotte.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.59,0:19:05.36,Default,,0,0,0,,She seems a little feather-headed so far, \Nbut mom is still the best! {careless person; scatterbrain; birdbrain; hasty person}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.36,0:19:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,95 out of 100! {she does say 100 but I assume it}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.08,0:19:08.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder what is Lotte doing now.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.85,0:19:11.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Has she been able to find her way around dad? {/getting along}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.03,0:19:16.93,Default,,0,0,0,,In the end, I couldn't bring myself to eat any omelette.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.93,0:19:19.17,Default,,0,0,0,,But it seems, nobody paid any attention to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.56,0:19:24.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Tonight, dad stays in his atelier \Non Kärntner Ring to work.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.51,0:19:27.54,Default,,0,0,0,,My impression of dad is 95 out of 100.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.54,0:19:30.76,Default,,0,0,0,,He may have his head in the clouds sometimes, \Nsometimes straight up childish. {/selfish and capricious}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.76,0:19:33.91,Default,,0,0,0,,But he's still cool and handsome. \NAnd so, so caring!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.15,0:19:37.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Today, I didn't really have a chance to talk to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.98,0:19:41.09,Default,,0,0,0,,But tomorrow, I made up my mind \Nto talk plenty to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.65,0:19:44.93,Default,,0,0,0,,On my part, tomorrow \NI'm starting my foray into cooking. {/i'll try to surmount/handle ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.93,0:19:47.36,Default,,0,0,0,,But I'm sick worried \Nabout whether or not I can do it. {/will I do it well - ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.53,0:19:51.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom, will it be good enough for you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.74,0:19:54.17,Default,,0,0,0,,My cooking.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.57,0:20:00.71,Default,,0,0,0,,In the cities, strange to them,{/foreign/alien/unknown}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.67,0:20:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,a stranger before - now is dad, or mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.54,0:20:10.85,Default,,0,0,0,,A day full of magic had finally come to an end.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.32,0:20:18.13,Default,,0,0,0,,But the excitements of tonight that the two experienced\Nwould hardly be forgotten any time soon.
